task.summary:
Created a base template which other templates can inherit.
Tested base template by returning it at the index page. Now uses flask bootstrap as well as Jinja2 templates. Can now begin migrating all pages to using templates.

Created a 404 page template
The 404.html template extends the base template. Modified the error handler for 404 in main.py to render the 404 template instead of a literal string.

Created a feedback page
Updated base.html to show a flash message (success) if they submitted feedback. Updated main to route everything for the feedback page. Updated requirements.txt to show the libraries we're using up to this point.

Added functionality to send email once feedback is submitted
Created the templates/mail directory for mail templates. Created the new_feedback.html and .txt files which will be used when sending email. Modified main.py to use flask mail. Configured the email settings using environment variables. Generated a secret key and moved that to environment variables. Created the send_email function to simplify sending mail. Modified the feedback view to grab the data from both the section and feedback areas of the form and send an email containing the data to the configured address. Updated the requirements.txt since new libraries are being used.

Added an index.html template.
index now renders a homepage which extends the base template instead of rendering the base template itself.
Moved body content into separate div from the page header div in feedback.html

Added contact info section
Created section for contact info within the index template.

Populated the teaching section with data
Modified the main.py file to add a new form class to be used in the index template. Modified the index view function to accept posts and redirect if the anonymous feedback button was hit. Modified the index template to display the data and the anonymous feedback button.
Populated the education section with data. Resolves #1

Populated the Honors and Awards Section. Resolves #14
Edited the index.html template to populate the Honors and Awards section.

Populated the Research Section. Resolves #15
Edited the index.html template to populate the research section.

Created a 500 error page template. Resolves #4
Edited the main.py file's internal server error view function to render the 500.html template. Also created the 500.html template. Simply displays that there was an internal server error.

Created a favicon. Resolves #6
Created a favicon. Modified base.html to link to the correct favicon based on what browser/device you're viewing from. Uploaded all the static icon files to the static folder.

Added gunicorn to requirements.txt. Resolves #18
Installed gunicorn with pip. Unfortunately it doesn't run on windows and there isn't a *nix machine lying around. Only matters for production deployment anyway though. The rest of the configuration will have to be handled in the ticket to deploy the app to heroku.
